# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SDK build-time env (OPTIONAL) — copy to .env.production ONLY for a
# dedicated multi-domain build, and fill in REAL hosts.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# By default the SDK ships ONE environment-agnostic bundle and resolves the
# backend AT RUNTIME from the <script src> origin (same-origin / single-domain
# reverse-proxy setups "just work" with no config). Do NOT commit a
# .env.production with placeholder hosts: `vite build` inlines these values, so
# placeholders bake a dead host into dist/ and break Start Recording / Copy Link.
#
# For a MULTI-DOMAIN deployment (separate internal/external hosts), prefer the
# RUNTIME override on the host page instead of a build-time env:
#
#   <script>
#     window.REMOTE_DEBUG_SDK_ENV = {
#       VITE_INTERNAL_HOST: 'https://internal.example.com',
#       VITE_EXTERNAL_WS:   'wss://external.example.com/socket.io',
#     };
#   </script>
#   <script src="https://external.example.com/sdk/index.umd.js"></script>
#
# Build-time values below are only consulted when there is no runtime override
# AND no caller-supplied default; real (non-placeholder) values are honoured.

VITE_INTERNAL_HOST=https://internal.example.com
VITE_INTERNAL_WS=wss://internal.example.com
VITE_EXTERNAL_HOST=https://external.example.com
VITE_EXTERNAL_WS=wss://external.example.com/socket.io
